title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare Vintage Marlin 1971 39D
postcontent: These guns are rare (this is a 39D, not an A)  and pretty hard to come across. There were only 16000 or so made in 1971 and when they do pop up they are usually in pretty rough condition. I really like this gun but it needs to belong to a collector who will appreciate more than I. It shoots great and is very accurate. Really fun to shoot. There are a few minor dings in the stock, as expected with the rifles age, and a small area of the bluing is scratched near the tip of the barrel where it looks like someone used too coarse steel wool to try to clean it. This will not show up in the photos and is nearly unnoticeable. Really nice grain pattern is present in the stock. Rifle, to the best of my knowledge, is not refinished and is in its original condition. This rifle will shoot 22LR 22L and 22S. I have more photos available upon request.

The wait time for one of these is over 2 years but you can have this one today.  I can send more detailed pictures on request.

70 series Colt 1911 
Other quality handguns/rifles (the evil black type)  

I am looking for at least 1k in cash plus trade.

Below is the write up from LaRue:

LaRue Tactical OBR 5.56 Overview:
Building off the success of our highly-accurate and reliable OBR 7.62, we set out to apply the same proven design features into a 5.56 rifle. The result is a lightweight, and reliable, tack driver that remains cool…even after high-rates of fire. The barrel and barrel nut does not touch the handguard at any point, so there is very little heat-transfer to your support hand. Like its 7.62mm sibling, both the upper and lower are CNC-machined from billet 7075-T6, for the optimum fit and consistency...translating into maximum accuracy. Even though this is a complete rifle, the upper will fit to any Mil-Spec AR15/M16 type lower.

 The continuous upper-rail provides plenty of room for weapon-mounted night-vision day/night combinations and provides correct ballistic orientation for all inline night-vision combinations. The 10 MOA cant gives users an added advantage when using magnified optics at longer distances. A step-down at the rear of the receiver creates zero MOA for use of BUIS’s at shorter distances.

 Each rifle ships with three, 3” long, MIL-STD-1913 detachable rail sections that they can be configured anywhere along the entire length of the handguard (via threaded steel inserts), for the interface of MIL-STD-1913 equipped lights, lasers, bipods, grips, tripod mounts, etc.

Barrels:
 The barrels are Stainless Steel in 12”, 16.1", 18" & 20" lengths. They are Wylde chambered, and feature polygonal rifling in a 1/8 twist rate. All barrels are threaded in ½ x 28, with an A2 flash hider attached (other muzzle devices can be added at an additional cost). The 12” model have carbine-length gas systems, the 16” and 18” models have a mid-length, and the 20” has a rifle-length. All gas blocks will feature our unique Port Selector Technology (PST), a two-point adjustable gas selector that allows optimum function between suppressed, and unsuppressed operation at the flip of a switch.

Internals:
 The Bolts and Bolt Carriers are hand-polished hard-chrome with max-staked carrier keys. The carrier key contact areas are surface-ground flat for zero gas leakage. The trigger group is the same excellent Geissele SSA Combat Triggers we use in the OBR 7.62.The SSA provides an average 4.5lb pull weight.(2.5 lbs on the first stage and 2lb on the second stage).

Furniture:
The 12”, 16”, and 18" models come with a 6-position Magpul CTR and LaRue medium A-PEG™ Grip. The 20” Model Comes with an A2 Stock, in black and LaRue medium A-PEG™ Grip.

title: For Sale:  EoTech SCAM!
postcontent:
The below link is for a cheap Chinese bootleg EOTech. It's a fake with and EOTech battery box. Don't be fooled!!!!!
http://www.armslist.com/posts/2239509/clarksville-optics-for-sale--l3-eotech-

First off EOTech does not make a model that has a green reticle. 
If the center "NV" button changes the reticle color, it's a fake. If the optics look like clear window glass, it's fake. If you can look inside the glass and see an LED, it's a fake. The reticle, on a real one, should seem a little fuzzy not crisp. If it feels cheap and not well made, likely a fake. If if has flip up lens covers that are cheesy and fall off easily, it's likely a fake. Lack of EOTech manufacturing and serial number sticker means it's likely a fake. Beware, people are swapping battery boxes with real EOTechs and putting them on fake ones as well as the EOTechs factory stickers. If the deal seams too good to be true, it's likely a fake.

Looking to sell or trade a French 1935A chambered in 7.65 French long. It was made in the S.A.C.M plant in France, and from the information I've gathered online, it was probably made in 1946 sometime shortly after WW2. It has a parkerized finish (it was never coated with the bake on enamel that the earlier ones had, as far as I can tell). It is in excellent condition, with some light wear on the edges. title: For Sale:  LaRue Tactical PredatOBR™ 7.62 BRAND NEW!        AR-10, AR, LARUE, LARUE TACTICAL
postcontent: The PredatOBR 7.62 was designed for those who are searching for a hybrid cross between the standard OBR and PredatAR 7.62x51 Rifles. The PredatOBR takes the highly accurate OBR 7.62 design, and lightens it in every possible way with the least-possible impact to the accuracy that the standard OBR is known for. The most remarkable feature of the PredatOBR is its ability to be completely “broken down” and stored into the supplied Roll-Bag and Tool Box. The PredatOBR handguard has a locking stainless steel QD Lever system on each side. Once the levers are released, the handguard slides off of the upper assembly in seconds. The PredatOBR's barrel can easily be removed with the supplied PredatOBR Barrel Wrench, unscrew the Barrel Nut from Receiver and pull the Barrel Assembly free from Receiver. No need to remove the gas tube, gas block or muzzle device. Reverse the process to reinstall. Hand-tighten Barrel Nut and torque approximately 1/8-turn past hand-tight (Approximately 40-50 foot pounds). Once reassembled correctly, the point of impact (POI) shift will be 0.0 to 0.5 MOA of the original. PredatOBR barrels are chambered in 7.62x51mm, and feature rifling in a 1/11.25 twist rate. All barrels are threaded in 5/8 x 24. Like the OBR and PredatAR riles, LaRue has eliminated the conventional AR barrel nut and bolt the handguard directly to the proprietary upper receiver, creating a true “free-float” barrel. The handguard does not touch the barrel or barrel nut at any place. The zero-MOA upper rail provides plenty of room for weapon-mounted night-vision day/night combinations. Both the upper and lower are CNC-machined from billet aluminum for the optimum fit and consistency. Even though it has been lightened certain features, there is still additional material in strategic areas to achieve maximum accuracy. The PredatOBR has threaded stainless-steel hard-points over the entire length of the handguard at the 3, 6, and 9 o’clock positions. These hard-points have an integral spine built-in for structural support. Provided with the system are three 3-inch MIL-STD-1913 rail sections that can be positioned anywhere along the handguard, per operator preference. These rail sections are attachable/detachable using a supplied tool (Torx® T-15 wrench). The rail sections are CNC-machined from billet aluminum. This robust solution provides a perfect precision mounting space for aiming lasers, illumination and bipods. The PredatOBR's Port Selector Technology™ (PST) gas block is adjustable, to aid in the optimum function when using a sound suppressor. This special gas block contains a dual port mechanism that is operated by rotating a lever from one side to another. When the lever is rotated to the right-side of the rifle, the gasses are reduced, to compensate for the extra blowback created by the suppressor. When rotated to the left side, the gasses are increased for use without a suppressor. The LaRue Tactical 6-position Retract Action Trigger (R.A.T.) Stock comes standard with every PredatOBR. It is ergonomic, has protected control surfaces and contains a set of cleaning rods in an internal compartment. Since the height of the 12 o’clock rail is at the optimum position, there is no need for a cheek riser as part of this system. Specifications: Caliber: 7.62 x 51 mm NATO Barrel Lengths: 14.5”,16.1”and 18” Rifling Twist Rate: 1/11.25 Barrel Life: 10,000 (approx) Gas System: Direct Impingement with LaRue PST™ port selector Accessories: 2ea, 20-Round LaRue Magazines 3ea 3” Rail Sections Operators Manual Carrying Case “Toolbox” Roll-Up Cloth Case Barrel Wrench Suppressor Compatibility: LaRue 7.62 rifles with Port Selector Technology (PST) have been optimized for best-performance with SureFire suppressors. We understand that there are dozens of 7.62 suppressors to choose from on the market at this time. We feel that SureFire suppressors fall somewhere in the middle-range in regards to effect of performance with gas-operated rifles. Many users have met with success operating different models of their choice. Combined with variables in ammunition, 7.62 suppressor owners have experienced a large spectrum of conditions (much greater than seen with 5.56 suppressors). This range of variables is easy to manage with a bolt-action 7.62, but with a gas-operated system it is not. While we made a concerted effort to design a gas system that will work with a wide range of suppressors, we can not guarantee proper-function with suppressor hardware other than SureFire. About the “Black Gold” Trigger: We are very proud to announce that we’ve selected the American Trigger Corporation AR Gold trigger to be installed in LaRue PredatOBRs going forward. These are a single stage trigger with take-up and a super short reset, similar in feel to a best-grade 1911 trigger, providing the optimum trigger action for a wide variety of shooting styles and disciplines. AR Gold Triggers have been used by some of the best competition shooters in the world for the last few years and dominate the top of the 3 Gun competition world. We have been testing and evaluating these triggers for well over a year, to ensure that they're up to our standard of quality. Our evaluation has shown the AR Gold to be magnificent and we're proud to include them as part of our new product line. One thing that is unusual about these triggers installed in our LaRue PredatOBRs, is they are treated with an IonBond black instead of American Trigger’s normal IonBond Gold.
